V. ATTACK OPERATING CHARACTERISTICS AND OPTIMAL
ATTACKS
We now study the impact of malicious data attack from the
perspective of an attacker. We assume that the attacker knows
the (MMSE) state estimator and the (GLRT) detector used by
the control center. We also assume that the attacker can choose
meters arbitrarily in which to inject malicious data. In practice,
however, the attacker may be much more limited. Thus, our
results here are perhaps more pessimistic than in reality.
